quoted-post.text: OPINION: In general, if you first bought #bitcoin in 2010-11, and don't have at least 5,000 bitcoin in cold storage, you screwed something up.  Likewise: 2012-13: Should still have 1,000+  2014-17: 10-100+ 2018-21: 1-10+ 2022-present: 0.1-1+  Most people "took profits" too soon and, thus, remain much poorer than they *should* have been had they simply hodled, traded less and/or more wisely managed/secured their bitcoin.

content: This tweet is hilarious. Some people in the early days had money and dumped a lot into Bitcoin, but most of us were poor as fuck.  I was an ideological retard selling baklava and cleaning toilets for bitcoin instead of getting a real job. You think I had $25,000 to invest in Bitcoin? 😂  Here's the reality: I have less bitcoin today than I did years back and I have no regrets. That's not a cope, it's the truth.  Maybe this is an unpopular take, but the last thing I care about doing is focusing my energy on acquiring more wealth once I can take care of myself & my family. I'd rather use that time for something better.  I'm still an ideological retard at heart, no matter what the price does.
